    "daily_lesson": {
      "term": "Momentum Investing",
      "explanation_en": "Momentum investing is a strategy of buying stocks that have been trending upward \u2014 using signals like RSI, MACD, and volume to confirm the move has real strength behind it. The idea is that assets that are rising tend to keep rising in the short term, driven by continued buyer interest and positive sentiment. Today's picks (JOBY, CLF) were chosen exactly this way: strong technical momentum in the sweet spot RSI range (55\u201370) before they become overbought.",
